{
  "texts": [
    "Although initial clinical trials have demonstrated promising results, it is uncertain how long the protection provided by the vaccines will last and what potential long-term side effects may be.",
    "Further, vaccine hesitancy and the factors that contribute to it are not fully understood.",
    "Moreover, the safety of COVID-19 vaccines in patients with chronic diseases (eg, chronic hepatitis, diabetes, heart failure, renal failure, and epilepsy) remains unknown.",
    "Precautionary MeasuresA total of 124 studies were related to precautionary measures implemented to prevent the spread of the virus.",
    "According to these studies, the effectiveness of many precautionary measures such as social distancing, wearing masks, hand hygiene, respiratory etiquette (eg, covering mouth and nose when coughing and sneezing), and ventilation systems is still unknown."
  ]
}